This paper focuses on the attitudes and concerns of older adults regarding online privacy, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also discusses theoretical implications for our understanding of privacy, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) or cryptography and security (cs.CR). The study involves in-depth interviews, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
